description.p:
According to an aspect, a switched-capacitor amplifier for amplifying an input signal comprises:
a first switch configured to couple the input signal to a first end of a sampling capacitor;
a second switch configured to couple a DC signal to a second end of the sampling capacitor;
a third switch configured to couple an output of a complementary push-pull amplifier to the first end of the sampling capacitor; and
a fourth switch configured to couple a first summing node of the complementary push-pull amplifier to the second end of the sampling capacitor.

According to an aspect, a switched-capacitor amplifier for amplifying an input signal comprises:
a first switch configured to couple the input signal to a first end of a first sampling capacitor and to a first end of a second sampling capacitor;
a second switch configured to couple a DC signal to a second end of the first sampling capacitor;
a third switch configured to couple a DC signal to a second end of the second sampling capacitor;
a fourth switch configured to couple an output of a complementary push-pull amplifier to the first end of the first sampling capacitor and to the first end of the second sampling amplifier;
a fifth switch configured to couple a first summing node of the complementary push-pull amplifier to the second end of the first sampling capacitor; and
a sixth switch configured to couple a second summing node of the complementary push-pull amplifier to the second end of the second sampling capacitor.

claim.claim-text:
A switched-capacitor amplifier for amplifying an input signal, comprising:
a first switch configured to couple the input signal to a first end of a sampling capacitor;
a second switch configured to couple a DC signal to a second end of the sampling capacitor;
a third switch configured to couple an output of a complementary push-pull amplifier to the first end of the sampling capacitor; and
a fourth switch configured to couple a first summing node of the complementary push-pull amplifier to the second end of the sampling capacitor.

A switched-capacitor amplifier for amplifying an input signal, comprising:
a first switch configured to couple the input signal to a first end of a first sampling capacitor and to a first end of a second sampling capacitor;
a second switch configured to couple a DC signal to a second end of the first sampling capacitor;
a third switch configured to couple a DC signal to a second end of the second sampling capacitor;
a fourth switch configured to couple an output of a complementary push-pull amplifier to the first end of the first sampling capacitor and to the first end of the second sampling amplifier;
a fifth switch configured to couple a first summing node of the complementary push-pull amplifier to the second end of the first sampling capacitor; and
a sixth switch configured to couple a second summing node of the complementary push-pull amplifier to the second end of the second sampling capacitor.
